Sentencas: An oxide electrode replacing Ni/YSZ anode for a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is desirable to reduce the carbon deposition under carbonaceous fuel.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: If this oxide material can simultaneously work as cathode, it will increase the simplicity and stability of an SOFC stack as in a symmetrical SOFC.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: However, the current oxide electrodes for symmetrical SOFCs are mostly p-type oxides showing compromised conductivity in reducing atmosphere, dictating a thin anode to reduce the ohmic loss.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: On the contrary, an n-type oxide showing superior electronic conduction in anode chamber will allow a thick anode support, giving room to a thin electrolyte and cathode to reduce the ohmic loss and the diffusion-related loss on the cathode side, respectively.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: A novel material Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-delta (FMTNM) with cations distributed randomly, based on n-type FeNbO4, is studied as both cathode and anode for an SOFC.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: This material synthesized in ambient air was stable in Ar-5% H-2 at 750 degrees C and showed higher electrical conductivity in reducing atmosphere than in air.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It was the first demonstration using an n-type oxide for both cathode and anode due to the conductivity arising from Fe2+/Fe3+ and Mo5+/Mo6+ transition.
Titulo: An n-Type Oxide Fe0.5Mg0.25Ti0.25Nb0.9Mo0.1O4-δ for Both Cathode and Anode of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
